							<body  ><div class="section"><p class="BillDebate"><strong>PATENTS (TRANS-TASMAN PATENT ATTORNEYS AND OTHER MATTERS) AMENDMENT BILL</strong></p><p class="SubDebate"><strong>In </strong><strong>Committee</strong></p><p class="Speech"><a name="time_20161102 20:37:58" ></a><strong>Hon RUTH DYSON (Labour—Port Hills)</strong>: I seek leave for all provisions of the Patents (Trans-Tasman Patent Attorneys and Other Matters) Amendment Bill to be taken as one debate, with separate votes on each at the end.</p><p class="Speech"><a name="time_20161102 20:38:21" ></a><strong>The CHAIRPERSON (Hon Chester Borrows)</strong>: Leave is put for that purpose. Is there any objection? There appears to be none.</p></div></body>
